name: cosy comfortable Irish cottage twin
description:
Our house is a cosy comfortable cottage with a large outdoor area for our guests to enjoy ,we are only 6 kilometres to the city centre with great transport links by bus & tram to the city centre & beyond
we have coffee shops ,restaurants , pubs & a large supermarket all about 5 mins walk from here ,
The bus stop is 2 mins away across the road from us & the tram station is a 10 min walk with trams going into the city every 5 mins or less ,
Our aim is make guests as comfortable as we can ,
neighborhood_overview:
I like our neighbourhood as there is no shortage of things to do ,there is a large Park nearby ,plus loads of restaurants and pubs & supermarkets ,
Everything is available a short walk away ,

The sea and the mountains are not far away and neither is the city it's 6 kilometres away ,all easily accessable
We are in a great location to explore the city & it's environs
host_about:
I am  a friendly outgoing Irishwoman ,who loves literature,travel and design.  I love meeting people and am always  fascinated at  how diverse we all are and yet we are all the very same ,I love travel and visiting new places and seeing all different cultures ,
I like having fun ,

name: Cosy Comfortable Irish Cottage  1 Double Bed
description:
Our Cottage is a charming light filled cottage in the vibrant district of Dundrum this area was noted in days gone by as a Spa resort ,
We have a terrific transport network locally ,the Luas a fast tram service in Dundrum will bring you to the city centre in 13 mins, the 14 bus is 2 mins from us ,
The 750 Dublin Coach Bus from the Airport stops locally & is 12 mins walk
There are loads of restaurants ,bars ,& shops within walking distance from our place ,
neighborhood_overview:
I love Dundrum and its surrounding areas ,
There is a huge Shopping Mall 10 mins walk from here with an enormous array of restaurants ranging from Jamie Oliver's to Mexican ,Thai Tapas Bars ,Italian there are a great variety of shops ,Harvey Nicholls ,Michael Kors ,,Hollister & some good pubs & restaurants in our village Churchtown..which is just down the road ,
There are great transport links ,great access to everywhere we are very near the city 4 miles away ,the mountains are about 8 miles away and the sea is 4 miles , the 750 Dublin Coach bus comes from the Airport to Dundrum village 10 mins walk from here ,what's not to like about that !

There are some lovely villages nearby ,Enniskerry is a lovely little village at the foot of the Dublin mountains & has a beautiful Palladian mansion & gardens worth visiting ,there is a bus locally that will take you there
Ranelagh is noted as a foodie village its about 2 miles from here & has some really good rest

name: 5.5 miles south of Dublin City :^)
description: A nice place to relax after the bustle of the city; close to the sea + not far from the Dublin Mountains ~ they are really hills. Clean, bright + fresh ~ with a garden to almost hide in.  TWO BEDROOMS + parking.  From Dublin Airport:  Aircoach 700 to 'STILLORGAN' plus 14 min. walk. Excellent, bus route to city ~ c.35 mins + LUAS/tram.  From €88/night for the first two guests ~ whether or not you use one or two rooms.  Extra guests : €35/night - inc. breakfast.  I live on the top floor.
neighborhood_overview: Close to the sea, hill walks and the city - via bus and car. It is a quiet neighborhood and my neighbors are friendly too.
host_about:
I live here on the third floor of my house.  The two bedrooms shown, and bathroom, are for exclusive use of guests, are all on the middle floor.  Kitchen, ground floor loo + garden are for sharing !

I am a freelance photographer + work extensively in the arts.  I am well travelled, both internally + externally, and have worked in 17 countries; including living in Paris (I have reasonable French) + Copenhagen (I have lousy Danish; although I can say strawberries + cream + 815 as that was my work number)  As regards sign language - I know the alphabet - so, I am a bit of a slow communicator on that front.

I am into social issues + sustainable living.

I have a clean bright home with a garden.

My friends are interesting . . . so are my guests, I've discovered.

Any questions just ask.

Books :  'LIFE - An Enigma a Precious Jewel' Daisaku Ikeda; 'Memoires' John McGahern; 'I Put a Spell on You' John Burnside; 'An Empire of the East - Travels in Indonesia' Norman Lewis; 'Shantaram' Gregory David Roberts.

Films :  Kes, Pixote, The Tin Drum, Münich, The English Patient, Withnail and I, My Left Foot, Annie Hall.

Music :  Jonathan Richman and The Modern Lovers, Ruben Gonzalez, Françoise Hardy, Toquiñho, Vinicius de Morais, Mehmet Ozan, Damien Rice, Rory Gallagher, Georgie Fame, Cat Stevens, Burl Ives, JJ Cale, Dory Previn, Ray LaMontagne, Credence Clearwater Revival, Emiliana Torrini, Georges Brassens, Georges Moustaki, Chopin.

Food :  tea & toast, Ovlatine, Marmite, Twiglets, Mediterranian, Middle Eastern, corn fed steak - rare - I'm a part-time vegetarian; curry, nuts/seeds/berries, juices + smoothies.

Airbnb motto :  'Communication is not a one way street !'

General motto : 'It's OK to break the rules if it creates value !'  ß:^)

Please note, as of 1st October 2022, gas and electricity prices have gone up by c.35%.  Some lights on as security are a good idea but a welcoming committee of lights is not required.  Your comprehension is appreciated.  [Never waste time, food or money]

description:
The apartment is top floor of a gated apartment complex a 2 minute walk from historic Kilmainham Gaol, 5 mins walk from beautiful Museum of Modern Art and 15 mins walk to the Guinness Storehouse Experience.

The apartment has 2 bed, 2 baths and is fully equipped!

name: Old World Converted Stables with Swimming Pool.
description:
The following is what past guests have said that they love about this property;
Guests commented on how old world and elegent it looks. You have a sense of being in the country with birds and squirrels in the trees but yet you are only 10 minutes to the airport and 10 minutes to the city centre.
Everyone adored our closeness to the phoenix park..There are many activities in the park including the zoo, the hop on hop off bus, segways, rent a bike to name a few.
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located at the gate of the famous Phoenix Park. The house has a beautiful country feel about it but yet it is 15 minutes from the City Centre. We are within 10 mins drive of 5 golf courses, so we are ideal for golf enthusiasts. We are only 20 minutes drive also from the Dublin mountains again ideal for hill walkers,and those that like horse riding.The village of Castleknock is 8 minutes walk from the house. Here you have 5 restaurants 3 pubs and all local amenities like hair dressers, dry cleaners, beauticians etc.
As we are at the Phoenix Park gate, our house is ideally situated for any event being held in the Phoenix park, like Bloom in June, Iron Man in August and motor racing and Dublin Marathon
host_about: Hi my name is Sarah and I am listing the lovely 'Old world converted stable yard' located in Dublin, Ireland.
amenities: 55 inch HDTV with standard cable, Netflix, Amazon Prime Video, premium cable
Private indoor pool - available all year, open specific hours, heated, pool cover, pool toys

name: Peaceful retreat for 5 - excellent location
description:
This apartment is quiet and peaceful and is a wonderful retreat at the end of a busy day sightseeing.

Excellent location for seeing the city of Dublin which can be reached in 10 minutes by bus or 30 min walk. Bus stops right outside the front door.

Supermarket 3 minute walk, pub/restuarants 10 min walk
Phoenix Park - 8 min walk
Dublin Zoo - 10 min walk
Playground - 10 min walk
Bike hire - 15 min
Airport transfer can be arranged for a fee
Keysafe available for guests arriving late
neighborhood_overview:
This street is a beautifully tree lined street which runs right up the the entrance of the Phoenix Park.
This park is the largest urban park in Europe and houses Dublin Zoo and the presidential home and offices as well as a children's playground. It is a wonderful park to visit and spans over 1750 acres.
The street also has beautiful Victorian red bricked houses all along it which date back to the 18th century so it really is a taste of old Dublin.
There is a major supermarket just 3 minutes walk as well as a pharmacy, bakery, coffee shops, bars, restuarants and many other amenities all within easy walking distance.
host_about: I grew up in the tourist business as my parents ran a hotel in Kildare so I have always wanted to get back into the hosptality industry.  I have owned this house from the early '90's when I returned from New York where I had lived for a number of years.  I have been in the buidling trade for the last 20 years so I thought I would combine the two and refurbish the house and provide rental accommodation in an extremely convenient locations to tourists.

neighborhood_overview: I love this area.  Trinity College is a ten minute walk. as is Grafton Street and Camden St.  The location cannot be beaten.  I love my street as it is friendly and tree-lined.  The convenience cannot be overestimated.   The neighbourhood is a great  Love being able to walk everywhere, and feeling part of history in Dublin's most historic residential quarter.mix of traditional Dublin and hipster gentrification.
host_about:
Hello.  I am a professional living in Dublin city centre with my husband.   I have lived abroad and love to travel.  My interests include food, cinema, reading and spending time with friends.  We love having people over for dinner and meeting new people.    We also love eating out.

Of the places I have visited for pleasure, I especially loved India, Bali, Brazil, Bolivia, Laos and Japan.  I really enjoy meeting people when I travel she getting local recommendations.  I love all of the Mediterranean and Hong Kong.  I love reading anything set in India or anything by Douglas Kennedy, Anne Tyler.  My monthly book club is something I really look forward to.

We have really enjoyed meeting new people through Airbnb.  We are pretty passionate about Dublin, and like to share all the places that we think are special with visitors.   Edgar says that Dubliners can be the most friendly people in the world!

We now have 2 cats living with us.   The cats will be on holiday when you rent our home.

name: Very Special Oval Georgian Studio
description: Experience authentic Georgian elegance is this unique large OVAL studio apartment, overlooking park.  Accommodates two in cosy sleeping loft. Cook dinner in the designer kitchen, and then head out to enjoy the attractions of the city.
neighborhood_overview:
A beautiful, historic residential square, built in 1790's, within 5-10 minutes walk of down-town city centre. Elegance and convenience combined with a bit of inner city grittiness. I have loved it all, since 1978!

Mountjoy Square is situated just NE of the historic city centre, within walking distance of just about all the main city attractions. It is the most densely populated area in the entire city: 1500 people have front doors opening onto the Square.

The house fronts onto a 4acre/1.5ha park, across a fairly busy street. This apartment faces the side street, so it is quieter, but you will still hear traffic.....Please bear in mind that this is NOT LEAFY SUBURBIA, but a vibrant, living city community and it's definitely gritty in places... Having said that, I have lived here, uneventfully, for nearly 38 years, and consider the trade-offs well worth it, for the excitement and convenience of having the city on my doorstep..
host_about: Architectural enthusiast & committed urbanite, Alexander technique teacher, daily swimmer. I love to cook and to share meals with friends, and I aspire  to grow at least some of my own food. I love where I live, and enjoy all the amenities the city has to offer. I am Secretary of the Mountjoy Square Society, whose aim is to improve our area for all who live work and visit here. I am also a committee member of the Irish Georgian Society, and I regularly organize  day trips and walking tours for our members.

Dublin two main pedestrian shopping streets, Grafton and Henry St are about 5 minutes away.
Trinity College with its famous Library is 3 minutes walk.

Dublin is experiencing a Renaissance after a long recession and every week a new exciting restaurant, cultural space or play is opening. It is a great time to be visiting!

name: City Centre Apartment | Temple Bar | Dublin Castle
description: Fantastic, top-floor, two-bedroom apartment in a beautiful, old building in the very, very heart of Dublin City. Dublin City is quite literally at your fingertips! This is the best located Airbnb listing in Dublin - and that's no exaggeration.
neighborhood_overview:
Have a glance at a map of Dublin and you'll see that Dame Street is right in the centre of everything that Dublin has to offer. Trinity College is at one end of Dame Street (3 minute walk from the apartment) and Christ Church Cathedral is at the other (2 minute walk in the other direction). On one side is Dublin Castle and City Hall, and on the other is Temple Bar.

All other notable parts of the city – such as Grafton Street area, St Stephens Green, Merrion Square, O'Connell Street – are within a 10-15 minute walk.

As well as being immersed in Dublin's history and culture, you're surrounded by the best cafes, restaurants, pubs and shopping in Dublin.
host_about: A native Dubliner back living in Dublin after stints in New York, London and the West of Ireland. Fond of travelling but always happy to get back to Dublin. The apartment I have listed is right in the very centre of Dublin City - very genuinely, it couldn't be any more central; the centre of the centre, if you like.

neighborhood_overview: Gracepark Guesthouse is located in the vibrant, leafy Drumcondra Village, between Dublin airport and the city centre. Drumcondra offers shops (Tesco, Lidl, pharmacies, etc) and a vast choice of restaurants, cafés, and pubs. In addition, Croke Park Stadium, the National Botanical Gardens, Glasnevin Cemetery. St. Patrick’s College & Dublin City University are all in or within walking distance of Drumcondra.

name: Chestnut view- 4* Rating Close to airport and city
description:
Our charming Town House is nestled in the quiet and sought-after location of Drumcondra. Perfectly situated near the city centre, St. Patrick's College, DCU, and Blanchardstown, it's an ideal spot for those seeking a city stay or short-term rental for work.Convenience is key, with a bus stop just 1 minute away.
Accommodating up to 5 people, our house provides ample space and comfort for your stay. Welcome to your home away from home in Drumcondra.
neighborhood_overview: The house is located on a quiet one way road with little traffic very close to the main road into the city or towards the airport.

name: Gracepark Guesthouse 2
description: Gacepark Guesthouse is a small, family run accommodation.  We pride ourselves on helping our guests get the most out of their stay in Dublin.  We have local knowledge and live on the same property, so we're always here to help!
neighborhood_overview: Gracepark Guesthouse is located in the vibrant, leafy Drumcondra Village, between Dublin airport and the city centre.  Its easy public transport links into the city centre make it the ideal place to stay to explore all the tourist sights while getting to experience the warmth and charm of the village. Drumcondra offers shops (Tesco, Lidl, pharmacies, etc) and a vast choice of restaurants, cafés, and pubs. In addition, Croke Park Stadium, the National Botanical Gardens, Glasnevin Cemetery. St. Patrick’s College & Dublin City University are all in or within walking distance of Drumcondra.
host_about: Hi, my name is Roy. I am 41 years old and have travelled extensively around the word. I run our small private 3-room guesthouse.  I am an avid sports spectator, love music, food and sharing my fair city, Dublin with guests. My wife and I have been married for 8 years, and we have two children.

name: Camden Central. Dublin at your door
description:
Quirky, arty house"

- A bright, spacious double room in the centre of Dublin. Literally 3 minutes from Stephen's Green (see map). And with TWO door to door BUS routes from AIRPORT. 16 & DAExpress.

This cosy room is at the top of it's own stairs in a 1930s apartment which faces on to Dublin's vibrant Camden St.
neighborhood_overview: Camden St is a vibrant shopping and socialising street which is one of the main arteries out of the city heading south. The only remaining street except for the famous Moore St. to have fruit and vegetable stalls. A great mix of the traditional and the modern.
host_about: I am an easy going, aging, musician, film maker and ESL teacher. A yoga aspirant, occasional sea swimmer and choir member.

name: Contemporary Victorian cottage
host_about: Hi my name is Aïda, I'm french and an artist.

name: Perfect Location City Centre House
description: Two bedroom period red brick terraced house on a quiet, tree-lined street in the heart of the city centre. Just off Patrick St.  There are two double bedrooms, one shower room, kitchen and living/dining room.  The house was fully refurbished and insulated.  It is very cosy and warm Roof terrace.  The interior is all white with some original features, including a working fireplace in the living room. WiFi, SMART TV, Apple TV.  Under floor heating downstairs..  This is our home.
neighborhood_overview:
It is right in the heart of the city centre and yet on a very quiet tree lined street. I like the traditional redbrick fronts of the houses and the fact that you can be in Temple Bar, Grafton Street or St Stephens Green in less than ten minutes. St Patrick's Cathedral and Christchurch and Christchurch Cathedral are minutes away. There is a great selection of traditional pubs and fashionable cafes.

Everything Dublin city centre has to offer is within walking distance.
host_about:
Hello.  I am a professional living in Dublin city centre with my husband.   I have lived abroad and love to travel.  My interests include food, cinema, reading and spending time with friends.  We love having people over for dinner and meeting new people.    We also love eating out.

Of the places I have visited for pleasure, I especially loved India, Bali, Brazil, Bolivia, Laos and Japan.  I really enjoy meeting people when I travel she getting local recommendations.  I love all of the Mediterranean and Hong Kong.  I love reading anything set in India or anything by Douglas Kennedy, Anne Tyler.  My monthly book club is something I really look forward to.

We have really enjoyed meeting new people through Airbnb.  We are pretty passionate about Dublin, and like to share all the places that we think are special with visitors.   Edgar says that Dubliners can be the most friendly people in the world!

We now have 2 cats living with us.   The cats will be on holiday when you rent our home.

name: self contained cozy tot private near city & airpor
description: Recently refurbished in January and  cosy spotless clean and warm and totally your own private and quiet and totally your own private space to relax and unwind in after a busy day of sightseeing in Dublin. This quiet place is 25 minutes from the city centre and also near beaches and fishing villages. A perfect getaway for all travellers. Please note any  unauthorised guests will result in the booking being cancelled without a refund
neighborhood_overview: Its nice and quiet yet near to the city center.
host_about: We are a couple who have three grown up children who have all left home so we have plenty of space to host people of all nationalities.

name: City living with garden, park, canal, luas
description: By the royal canal, 3 minutes from the Luas light rail with light filled extension
neighborhood_overview: We waited for a house to become available in this Phibsboro neighbourhood because we knew how much families loved to bring up kids here. The community spirit in Shandon help drive the annual street party with kids sports and a giant banquet, the Christmas carol singing around the streets, Halloween festivities, and the local Phizzfest. The Royal Canal passes only minutes away and is ideal for a jog, a stroll or a bike ride. A range of small independent shops are ten minutes walk away- great deli & gift store, fruit & veg store, fine butcher and fishmonger and a large supermarket ten minutes the other direction. Within 20 minutes you can walk to Dublin City centre and  the National Botanic Gardens- one of Dublin's treasures and Glasnevin Cemetery and Museum. Thirty minutes walk brings you to Phoenix Park (the biggest urban park in Europe) and Dublin zoo. The house provides easy access to numerous museums and galleries, including Collins Barracks or the Museum of Modern Art. The Gravedig
host_about: We live in Phibsboro in Dublin, with our three kids; Johnny travels around the world with work so when we get a chance we like to travel to Leamcon to unwind from city life and let the kids have a taste of country life. We cook fish that we buy from fishermen in the locality or mussels we pick ourselves and hang out in front of the fire and play cards.

name: Cosy, self-contained, 1-bed space.
description: Clean, private and spacious self-contained space, suit couple. About 20 mins walk to O'Connell Street. Fully fitted bathroom, kitchen/living room, separate double bedroom. Near shops, pubs, and public transport.  Suit quiet, non-smoking couple. Very good public transport, including the newly extended tram. You can get a tram just a few minutes walk away from the flat and it's only 4 stops into O'Connell Street!
neighborhood_overview:
Phibsborough (also spelled Phibsboro) is very convenient in that it is near to all amenities, e.g. shops, cafes and public transport. It is also within easy access to the centre of the City, so guests can choose to avail of the tranquility of their apartment or the busy nightlife of the city.
Convenient to Croke Park, The Botanic Gardens, The Phoenix Park and Glasnevin Museum. Also within easy reach of the Gate Theatre, Dublin Writers' Museum and other attractions.
It's even easier to get to the city centre now, using the newly opened Luas tram line. Only 4 stops to O'Connell Street!
host_about: I'm from Co. Mayo, in the West of Ireland. I work part-time as an administrator. I have a grown-up son.

name: Great house in vibrant Stoneybatter
description:
Come and stay in Dublin’s shortest street - in vibrant Stonybatter.
The place is compact,warm, quiet, safe and secure.
It’s central location makes it a great base to explore the city.
A kitchen diner, two double bedrooms plus two bathrooms and a small covered yard.
Great for families with small children, couples & business travelers.
Not for house parties.
Bars/Restaurants, Shops, Laundry, LUAS trams, Dublin Bus, on your doorstep.
CHK IN 15.00pm - 21.30pm.
neighborhood_overview:
In vibrant Stonybatter, beside a former convent where Robin Hood's pal, Little John lived.
Academic quarter: TUD college campus 200m; The Law Society Solicitors school 400m; The King's Inns Barrister Law school 400m.
History: Saint Michan's Church Crypts 400m. GUINNESS storehouse 800m. Jameson Whiskey museum 300m. Collins Barracks museum 600m.
host_about:
Welcome to my Hometown of Dubh Linn, Baile Átha Cliath, or plain ‘auld’ Dublin City Ireland.
I know my native city like the back of my hand.
I’m a Failte Ireland Approved National Tour Guide for Ireland.
I used to write news reports but during Covid I learned to drive tour buses so that’s what I do now.
My house is central, secure, clean and warm.  There’s lots to do in Dublin City Ireland, so stop looking, start booking.

name: Large 5 Star Prime South Dublin House
description: Large modern semi-detached home suitable for families. All modern conveniences, great transport location for both Dublin and Wicklow. Lovely decking area with BBQ. We are experienced Airbnb hosts and we take your comfort seriously. You can assume that the house will be spotlessly clean on arrival, all of our listed facilities will be available, and that your family will enjoy comfort and safety. Our gated property ensures that children are safe and free to play in the garden. Relax and enjoy!
neighborhood_overview: Dundrum is one of the best neighbourhoods in south Dublin. We have fantastic amenities closeby in the form of the Dundrum Town Centre with lots of great restaurants and shopping facilities. Transport to the city is close by in the form of our tram systems (LUAS) which is close, convenient and very reliable. We are also close to the beautiful Marley Park with hundreds of acres of woodland. Wicklow is a short drive away with easy access to all of the major attractions including Glendalough and Avoca. The house is accessed from the M50 motorway which has a direct link to Dublin Airport - journey by car to the house from the airport is about 25 minutes.
host_about: We have a large family who are now either leaving home or are living away for the moment. We also live in Wicklow during the Summer so our house is available. As an avid piano player I have a nice piano available and lots of sheet music to practice with!
amenities: 45 inch HDTV with Disney+, Netflix, premium cable, Roku, standard cable, DVD player

name: No1 friendly family home
description: This room is for minimum stay of 1 month only
host_about: We are an out going family of five.We are a family that likes to welcome home stays & enjoy meeting new people , learning new cultures & share our welcoming Irish culture too. Our house is always buisy & you certainly won t feel lonely here, we like to treat our guests like one of the family & always have time to chat . So if you are coming from another country & are looking for a warm friendly family environment but with the luxury of your own private room & bathroom, that's here. 3 Double rooms to rent with en-suite & tv, with full use of all amenities of the house, wifi, fully equipped kitchen, guest fridge, games room, playstation & Wii , threadmill , washing machine, dryer, garden.
